<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2669&amp;p=19582#p19582"><![CDATA[
Why is a fixed bank necessary? I don't see why a few bytes of reset code couldn't be placed in all banks to free ORs.<br /><br />Also, what about mirroring? A 2 bit MUX can be built with a single 7400, then all you'd need is a register bit.  With 3 more NAND-2s you could get SRAM decoding: !(Phi2 &amp;&amp; nCE &amp;&amp; A14 &amp;&amp; A13) = nWRAMCE<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Fri Nov 17, 2006 6:43 pm</p><hr />
